OVERVIEW
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

BG Remover: Background Eraser ("the App", "we", "our") is a
background removal application for Android. This Privacy Policy explains
how we handle your data when you use our App.

THE SHORT VERSION:
We do not collect, store, transmit, or share any of your personal data
or photos. All image processing happens entirely on your device. Your
photos never leave your phone.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. INFORMATION WE COLLECT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

We do NOT collect any of the following:
  • Personal information (name, email address, phone number, etc.)
  • Photos, images, or any media files you process in the App
  • Location data
  • Device identifiers or advertising IDs
  • Usage analytics or behavioral data
  • Crash reports or diagnostic data
  • Any form of account or profile information

The App does not require you to create an account or log in.
The App does not require an internet connection to function.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2. HOW THE APP PROCESSES YOUR PHOTOS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

All image processing in BG Remover is performed entirely on your
device using Google ML Kit, which is a local, on-device machine
learning library provided by Google.

  • Your photos are NEVER uploaded to any server.
  • Your photos are NEVER transmitted over the internet.
  • Processing happens locally in your phone's memory.
  • Processed results are saved only to your device's local storage
    (specifically, the Pictures/BGRemover folder on your phone).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3. PERMISSIONS WE REQUEST AND WHY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The App requests the following Android permissions:

  READ_MEDIA_IMAGES (Android 13+) /
  READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (Android 12 and below):
    → Required to let you select photos from your gallery for
      background removal. We only read the specific image you choose.
      We do not scan, index, or access any other files.

  WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (Android 9 and below):
    → Required to save the processed (background-removed) image to
      your gallery. On Android 10+, this is handled without this
      permission using scoped storage.

  CAMERA:
    → Required only if you choose to use the in-app camera feature to
      capture a new photo directly. This permission is optional —
      you can use the App without granting camera access by choosing
      images from your gallery instead.

  VIBRATE:
    → Used for haptic feedback (subtle vibration) when interacting
      with buttons. No data is involved.

  POST_NOTIFICATIONS:
    → Used to show processing progress notifications. No data is
      transmitted. This permission is optional.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
4. GOOGLE ML KIT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

BG Remover uses Google ML Kit's Subject Segmentation API for
on-device background removal. This library runs entirely on your
device and does not send image data to Google's servers.

For more information on Google ML Kit's data practices, please refer
to Google's Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
5. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The App does not integrate any third-party advertising SDKs,
analytics platforms, crash reporting tools, or social media SDKs.

The App does not display advertisements.
The App does not track you across other apps or websites.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
6. DATA STORAGE AND RETENTION
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The only data stored by the App is:

  • A local database (Room/SQLite) on your device that stores
    references (file paths) to your processed images and their
    metadata (file name, dimensions, file size, date processed).
    This data never leaves your device.

  • App settings and preferences (edge softness, sensitivity,
    output format, etc.) stored locally via Android DataStore.
    This data never leaves your device.

You can delete all locally stored data at any time by:
  • Using the "Clear History" button within the App
  • Uninstalling the App (removes all App data)
  • Going to Android Settings → Apps → BG Remover: Background Eraser → Clear Data

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
7. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The App does not collect any data from any user, including children.
The App is suitable for all ages. Since we collect no personal
information, the App complies with the Children's Online Privacy
Protection Act (COPPA) and similar regulations worldwide.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
8. SECURITY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Since all data is processed and stored locally on your device, the
security of your images depends on your device's security settings
(screen lock, encryption, etc.). We have no access to your data and
therefore no ability to breach it.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
9. YOUR RIGHTS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Since we do not collect any personal data, there is no data for us
to provide, correct, or delete on our end. All data related to your
use of the App resides only on your device and is entirely within
your control.

If you wish to delete all data associated with the App, simply
uninstall it from your device.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
